article.headline: Oregon State 87, Portland State 58
article.story:
CORVALLIS, Ore. (AP) -- Kim Butler had a career-high 31 points to
lead Oregon State to an 87-58 win over Portland State on Tuesday.

Oregon State used a 23-2 first-half run to break the game open.
The Beavers led 52-21 at the half, and the Vikings couldn't get
closer than 18 points in the second half.

Anita Rivera added a career-high 19 points and eight rebounds
for Oregon State (5-1).

Kelsey Kahle had 22 points for Portland State (5-3).
